		<td><b>Re: Doing 14x16 square tiles is possible</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That or if you're porting a block puzzle game designed for a platform without wide pixels, where 8x8 is too small and 16x16 is too big. <em>Puyo Pop</em> for Game Boy Advance uses 2 layers to display 12x12-pixel tiles, as does the homebrew <em>Luminesweeper</em>. <em>Zoop</em> for Super NES uses software rendering for 12x14-pixel tiles.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


